brewery.brewery_description:
From little things, big things grow
Warrandyte Brewing Co. is the newest kid on the block in the craft beer scene. Locally owned and Melbourne made, our beer is brewed for the community and all craft beer lovers.
 

A passion for craft beer and appreciation for the community planted the idea whilst we were living in Canada. It wasnâ€™t until we were in the depths of a lockdown back in Melbourne that the concept grew into something great.
 

WBCo. has worked tirelessly on our recipe development and we pride ourselves on brewing the highest quality of craft beers. Our dream is to one day have a physical presence in the riverside town, but for now we are focusing on developing killer beers for you, which you can in the fridge at your local bottle shop or venue. 



We hope through our beer we can bring the community back together, out of isolation and into social gatherings with family and friends.

beer.beer_description: Flowing with bold flavour. The Yarra Red is a hoppy red ale that balances rich malt character with bursts of citrus, tropical fruit and stone fruit aromas. Inspired by Warrandyte's rugged bushland, red gums, and golden history, it's a celebration of place and people.

Brewed as a traditional Schwarzbier, this easy drinking, crisp dark Lager has hints of chocolate and coffee on the nose and on the taste buds. Tipping our hat at tradition, whilst putting our own unique spin on a great winter beer.

This traditional Helles Lager is brewed with noble German hops and a classic malt bill that makes this lager so clean and crisp. 

Warrandyte Lager has been brewed the OG way, crafted using traditional hops & malt means this lager is a true tongue pleaser. The subtle spice and floral flavours makes this lager a thirst crushing addition for just about anywhere at any time. So dig deep into the esky, grab a cold one and enjoy the experience.

No one forgets their first krush, think back to that backyard party, backpack on, warm beers stashed away. This beer reminds us of the good old days. Krush cold IPA is a smooth mover, jam packed with Krush Hop as its hero, this cold IPA is one to remember.
